{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011qWAqihJGVpp5Ls1DkLiGH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification criteria pass:\n\n1. **Cluster health: green** — 3 nodes, 0 unassigned shards, 100% active shards\n2. **All nodes in `/_cat/nodes`** — es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2 all present\n3. **app-data readable** — returns the seeded document `{\"msg\":\"seed\"}`\n\n**Root cause:** The precondition script used a bash heredoc to update the configmap, which caused `${POD_NAME}` to be expanded to an empty string (making `node.name` blank, which ES rejects as a parse error), and also used wrong FQDN seed hosts pointing to the `default` namespace instead of `elasticsearch`.\n\n**Fix:** Restored the configmap from the original resource file — which keeps `${POD_NAME}` as a literal string (ES 7.x natively expands env vars in `elasticsearch.yml`) and uses the correct short-form service names (`es-cluster-0.es-cluster`). Deleted the broken es-cluster-2 pod so the StatefulSet recreated it with the correct config."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":958,"cache_read_input_tokens":41002,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":958},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8fff7789-00a7-40dc-acfc-d1fd188e8d18","uuid":"21a1b66b-09e4-4920-8934-9485d5026b68","request_id":"req_011CcMVnvwzsFAPGkMNJZ2b1"}
